1 NOTE Was baptized catholic, but then abandoned by her father who re married.
2 CONT Abandoned the catholic faith when she married her husband Nang.
2 CONT Was a resourceful and loving mother.  She raised chicken, and would eat
2 CONC  a raw egg by inserting a pin, which she would pull off the turban hold
2 CONC ing her long hair coiled around her head, prick the egg, and suck up th
2 CONC e yolk.  She was known to cross the Chinese border on horseback to deal
2 CONC  in counterfeited goods.  So grand mother was a regular horseback ridin
2 CONC g highway bandit in her time!
2 CONT After 1954, she was never re united with her husband Nang.  She did man
2 CONC age to visit Saigon once after 1975, but by then Nang had fled with his
2 CONC  sons and their family to the US.  She had met with Minh, who was the s
2 CONC ister of her daughter in law Diep.  The two must have got talking about
2 CONC  the Catholic faith, because not long after, she was re baptized and re
2 CONC  accepted into the Catholic church by cha Tong, who was the head priest
2 CONC  at Hanoi's cathedral, and who was also brother to Diep and Minh.
2 CONT When Tin died, she had a cathlolic burial mass said for her by Tong.
